President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring January 2012 as National Slavery and Human Trafficking Prevention Month. The proclamation recognizes the ongoing issue of modern slavery and human trafficking, both within the United States and around the world. It emphasizes the need for international partnerships and cooperation to combat these crimes and protect the rights of victims. The proclamation also calls upon the American people to educate themselves about modern slavery and human trafficking and to participate in programs and activities aimed at ending these injustices.